## Your task

You are given a list of partial summaries, each produced from a different batch of the same evaluation's results. Each partial summary contains an overall assessment, patterns (with titles, descriptions, frequencies, and example generation IDs), and recommendations.

Consolidate them into ONE final summary:
- Merge patterns that describe the same underlying theme across batches into a single pattern. Keep the clearest title and description, and combine their example generation IDs (keep 1-5 representative IDs per pattern).
- Re-judge each merged pattern's frequency across the whole set: "common" (appears across most batches / the majority of runs), "occasional" (several), "rare" (few).
- Write a single overall_assessment (1-2 sentences) reflecting the full evaluation, not any single batch.
- Consolidate the recommendations into the 2-4 most important, actionable ones, deduping overlaps.

{% if filter == 'all' %}
Keep patterns in all three categories (pass, fail, N/A) where present.
{% elif filter == 'pass' %}
Only pass_patterns are relevant. Leave fail_patterns and na_patterns as empty arrays.
{% elif filter == 'fail' %}
Only fail_patterns are relevant. Leave pass_patterns and na_patterns as empty arrays.
{% elif filter == 'na' %}
Only na_patterns are relevant. Leave pass_patterns and fail_patterns as empty arrays.
{% endif %}

IMPORTANT GUIDELINES:
- Limit to 0-4 patterns per category after merging.
- Preserve real example_generation_ids from the partial summaries; do not invent new ones.
- Recommendations should be specific and actionable (2-4 total).
- The statistics you return are not used and may be left as zeros; the caller computes the ground-truth counts.
